y-hero-shell\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"city-hero-copy\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"hero-breadcrumbs\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"$L11\",null,{\"href\":\"/\",\"children\":\"Home\"}],[\"$\",\"i\",null,{\"className\":\"bi bi-chevron-right\"}],[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"children\":\"Dog Parks Directory\"}],[\"$\",\"i\",null,{\"className\":\"bi bi-chevron-right\"}],[\"$\",\"strong\",null,{\"children\":\"Murfreesboro\"}]]}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"hero-eyebrow\",\"children\":\"Diamond City Dogs\"}],[\"$\",\"h1\",null,{\"children\":\"Dog Parks in Murfreesboro, TN\"}],\"$undefined\",[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"hero-description\",\"children\":\"Murfreesboro offers well-equipped facilities like the Murfreesboro Bark Park and an extensive greenway system perfect for active dogs and owners.\"}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"city-rich-description\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"p\",\"0\",{\"className\":\"rich-description-paragraph\",\"children\":[\"Murfreesboro, TN, has developed into a highly dog-friendly city, with an estimated 60% of households owning at least one dog. The \",[\"$\",\"$L11\",\"1\",{\"href\":\"https://www.murfreesborotn.gov/Facilities/Facility/Details/Murfreesboro-Bark-Park-28\",\"target\":\"_blank\",\"rel\":\"noopener noreferrer\",\"className\":\"rich-link\",\"children\":\"Murfreesboro Bark Park\"}],null,\" serves as the central off-leash facility, featuring separate fenced areas for small and large dogs, water stations, and even river access. For extended adventures, the \",[\"$\",\"$L11\",\"4\",{\"href\":\"https://www.murfreesborotn.gov/Facilities\",\"target\":\"_blank\",\"rel\":\"noopener noreferrer\",\"className\":\"rich-link\",\"children\":\"Stones River Greenway System\"}],null,\" provides over 17 miles of paved multi-use trails, perfect for long walks, jogs, or bike rides with leashed companions. Nearby, \",[\"$\",\"$L11\",\"7\",{\"href\":\"https://www.nps.gov/stri\",\"target\":\"_blank\",\"rel\":\"noopener noreferrer\",\"className\":\"rich-link\",\"children\":\"Stones River National Battlefield\"}],null,\" offers historic trails where leashed dogs can explore alongside their owners.\"]}],[\"$\",\"p\",\"1\",{\"className\":\"rich-description-paragraph\",\"children\":[\"The community's pet-friendly culture is reinforced by events like \\\"Bark In The Boro\\\" and venues such as \",[\"$\",\"$L11\",\"1\",{\"href\":\"https://maydaybrewery.com/\",\"target\":\"_blank\",\"rel\":\"noopener noreferrer\",\"className\":\"rich-link\",\"children\":\"Mayday Brewery\"}],null,\", which welcomes all dogs regardless of size or breed to its tasting room and patio. The city has also hosted prestigious canine events like the Cynosport Dog Agility World Games. While Murfreesboro's outdoor amenities are impressive, Tennessee's summer heat and humidity can pose challenges. \",[\"$\",\"$L11\",\"4\",{\"href\":\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/\",\"target\":\"_blank\",\"rel\":\"noopener noreferrer\",\"className\":\"rich-link\",\"children\":\"Indoor Dog Park\"}],null,\" provides a vital climate-controlled alternative, ensuring Murfreesboro's large dog population can maintain their exercise routines safely and comfortably throughout the year.\"]}]]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"hero-cta-row\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"$L10\",null,{\"className\":\"hero-cta primary\",\"targetId\":\"park-directory\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"i\",null,{\"className\":\"bi bi-list-check\"}],\"Browse directory\"]}],[\"$\",\"$L10\",null,{\"className\":\"hero-cta ghost\",\"targetId\":\"map-and-neighborhoods\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"i\",null,{\"className\":\"bi bi-geo-alt\"}],\"Open map\"]}],[\"$\",\"$L11\",null,{\"href\":\"/list-your-park\",\"className\":\"hero-cta text-link\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"i\",null,{\"className\":\"bi bi-plus-circle\"}],\"Submit a park\"]}]]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"hero-footnotes\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",\"15+ verified spots\",{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"i\",nul